Limelight->Render:

This has the same functionality as the "Render" button in the Render
Options editor -- it starts up the rendering operation. It has also
been provided in the Limelight menu to quickly access this feature.
Typically, you setup the rendering parameters to the desired values in
the Render Options editor and then use the Render button afterwards.

When you click on "Render", you will notice your cursor change to a
"stop watch" cursor and the hand on the stop watch will start to move
to indicate that Movieola is setting up data for the rendering
process. When the hand on the stop watch completes one full circle, it
means that Movieola has finished setting up the data and rendering is
about to start.

